---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Download | market-data-recorder">
  <section class="page-hero compact">
    <p class="eyebrow">Downloads</p>
    <h1>Get the Windows build, or build from source today.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      GitHub Releases is the place to download packaged builds. If the latest release is not live yet, the source path below works immediately.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a class="button primary" href="https://github.com/Zwin-ux/arbitrage/releases" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Open GitHub Releases</a>
      <a class="button secondary" href="/docs">Build from source</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="download-grid">
    <article class="download-card">
      <p class="eyebrow">Recommended</p>
      <h2>Windows installer</h2>
      <p>Look for <code>market-data-recorder-setup.exe</code> in the latest GitHub release.</p>
      <ul class="signal-list">
        <li>Creates shortcuts and uninstall support</li>
        <li>Includes app docs, license, and notices</li>
        <li>Supports launch-at-login during install</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
    <article class="download-card">
      <p class="eyebrow">Portable</p>
      <h2>Windows bundle zip</h2>
      <p>Look for <code>market-data-recorder-app-portable.zip</code> if you want the portable app folder instead of the installer.</p>
      <ul class="signal-list">
        <li>Contains the app executable and runtime files</li>
        <li>No installer required</li>
        <li>Best for testing and isolated environments</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
    <article class="download-card">
      <p class="eyebrow">Need it now</p>
      <h2>Source build</h2>
      <p>If Releases is empty, use the repo directly:</p>
      <pre><code>python -m pip install -e ".[dev]"
market-data-recorder-app</code></pre>
      <p>That gets you the desktop app without waiting for a packaged binary.</p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
